HEADWORD: Imperforated
<hw>Im*per"fo*ra"ted</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. pref. <ets>im-</ets> not +
<ets>perforatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>perforate</ets> to perforate. See
<er>Perforate</er>.]</ety> <def>Not perforated; having no opening or
aperture.</def> <rj><au>Sir J. Banks.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

